╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗
║  HELIX TRAINER — Exercise 1.5: Scrolling and Jumps              ║
║  Category: Movement              Difficulty: ★☆☆ Fundamental    ║
╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝

COMMANDS TO LEARN
─────────────────
  Ctrl-d    Half page down
  Ctrl-u    Half page up
  Ctrl-f    Full page down
  Ctrl-b    Full page up
  Ctrl-o    Jump backward on jumplist
  Ctrl-i    Jump forward on jumplist
  z z       Center current line on screen (view mode)

INSTRUCTIONS
────────────
  This exercise has many lines. Scattered through them are lines
  marked with >>> that contain a word in CAPS. Collect all the
  CAPS words and write them on the ANSWER line at the bottom,
  separated by spaces.

  Use Ctrl-d/Ctrl-u to scroll quickly. Use / to search if you
  want, but try scrolling first to build the habit.

────────────────────────── PRACTICE ──────────────────────────────

Line 1: The weather is nice today.
Line 2: Nothing special here.
Line 3: Just some filler text.
>>> The first word is HELIX
Line 5: More ordinary content.
Line 6: Keep scrolling down.
Line 7: Almost there.
Line 8: Not yet.
Line 9: Patience.
Line 10: The journey is the reward.
Line 11: Still going.
Line 12: Regular line.
>>> The second word is MODE
Line 14: More content ahead.
Line 15: Keep looking.
Line 16: Nothing here either.
Line 17: Just a bit more.
Line 18: Getting closer.
Line 19: Almost at the next one.
Line 20: Here we go.
>>> The third word is ROCKS
Line 22: Final stretch.
Line 23: One more section.
Line 24: Nearly done.
Line 25: Last filler line.

ANSWER: REPLACE THIS WITH THE THREE WORDS

────────────────────────── EXPECTED ──────────────────────────────

Line 1: The weather is nice today.
Line 2: Nothing special here.
Line 3: Just some filler text.
>>> The first word is HELIX
Line 5: More ordinary content.
Line 6: Keep scrolling down.
Line 7: Almost there.
Line 8: Not yet.
Line 9: Patience.
Line 10: The journey is the reward.
Line 11: Still going.
Line 12: Regular line.
>>> The second word is MODE
Line 14: More content ahead.
Line 15: Keep looking.
Line 16: Nothing here either.
Line 17: Just a bit more.
Line 18: Getting closer.
Line 19: Almost at the next one.
Line 20: Here we go.
>>> The third word is ROCKS
Line 22: Final stretch.
Line 23: One more section.
Line 24: Nearly done.
Line 25: Last filler line.

ANSWER: HELIX MODE ROCKS

──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
HINTS (read only if stuck):
  Hint 1: Use Ctrl-d to scroll down half a page at a time.
  Hint 2: When you find a >>> line, note the CAPS word.
  Hint 3: After finding all three words, navigate to the ANSWER
          line and use c to change the placeholder text.
  Hint 4: Try z z to center the current line if you lose track
          of where you are.
